From fdebd6ee9f95fa86f7752502ec511e96c3d26339 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: dijiuyue <873487783@qq.com>
Date: Sat, 9 May 2026 21:18:08 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] fix: format title numbers, figure/table captions consistently

Replace per-run formatting with format_all_runs_in_paragraph() which walks
the entire paragraph XML tree (.//w:r) to catch runs nested inside fields,
hyperlinks, and other elements that python-docx's para.runs misses.

Also add sync_numbering_with_titles() to update numbering.xml definitions
so auto-generated multilevel list numbers match title formatting.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
